@peace2000

Firefox needs that removeparam filter as they use a slightly different ad solution (or used to), never needed to use it for Chromium browsers.

I also just got an ad slip through on Chromium now (on tv4play), but it's hard to reproduce. Maybe there's a race condition somewhere as Chromium may be slower with scriptlets, but I never had an ad slip through on Firefox. Do you get any ads slip through if you add `mtv.fi##+js(xml-prune, MediaFiles, , videoplaza.tv/proxy/distributor)` instead of `mtv.fi##+js(xml-prune, MediaFile, , fi-mtv3.videoplaza.tv/proxy/distributor)` ?

@Alex-302 I'm pretty sure it is caused by enhanced blocking. I've disabled it in safari-settings and had no issues since. 

macOS 13.6 (22G120)
Safari 17.0 (18616.1.27.111.22, 18616)
